nanenstaude|f}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|μπανανιά|f}}\n* Hawaiian: {{tt|haw|maiʻa}}\n* Ido: {{tt+|io|bananiero}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|pisang}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|crann bananaí|m}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|banano|m}}\n* Javanese: {{tt+|jv|gedhang}} {{qualifier|ngoko}}, {{tt|jv|pisang}} {{qualifier|krama}}\n* Kadazan:\n*: Coastal Kadazan: {{t|kzj|punti}}\n* Lao: {{t-needed|lo}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|pala|f}} {{qualifier|classical}}\n* Latvian: {{tt+|lv|banāns|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt+|mk|бана́на|f}}\n* Malay: {{tt|ms|pokok pisang}}\n*: Brunei Malay: {{tt|kxd|puhun pisang}}, {{tt|kxd|pukuk pisang}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt+|ml|വാഴ}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|banana}}\n* Mon: {{tt|mnw|[[တၞံ]][[ဗြာတ်]]|tr=tnaṁ brāt}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|bananplante|m|f}}\n* Occitan: {{tt+|oc|bananièr|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|bananowiec|m}}, {{tt+|pl|banan|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bananeira|f}}\n* Romagnol: {{tt|rgn|banân|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|bananier|m}}, {{tt+|ro|banan|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|бана́н|m}}, {{t|ru|[[банановый|бана́новое]] [[де́рево]]|n}}\n* Sanskrit: {{tt+|sa|कदल|n}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|бана́на|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|banána|f}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|banánovník}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|bananovec|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|bananero|m}}, {{t+|es|banano|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|mgomba}}\n* Swedish: {{tt|sv|bananplanta}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|puno ng saging}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|வாழை}}\n* Tatar: {{tt|tt|банан}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|అరటిచెట్టు}}, {{tt|te|అంటిచెట్టు}}\n* Tetum: {{tt|tet|hudi}}, {{tt|tet|hudi-hun}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|ต้นกล้วย}}\n* Tibetan: {{t-needed|bo}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt|vi|([[cây]]) [[chuối]]}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|coed bananas|f-p}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|color}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|banane}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t-check|cmn|[[香蕉]][[顏色]]|tr=xiāngjiāo yánsè}}, {{tt|cmn|香蕉色|tr=xiāngjiāosè}}\n* Dutch: {{tt|nl|bananengeel|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt|fi|banaaninkeltainen}}\n* Ido: {{tt|io|bananea}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|바나나색}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|pisang}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|bananowy}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt|pt|amarelo-banana}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|banan}}\n* Welsh: {{tt|cy|melyn banana}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|pejorative: person of Asian descent}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|香蕉人|tr=xiāngjiāorén}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|vinosilmä}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{en-adj|-}}\n\n# Curved like a banana, especially of a ball in flight.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2001|author=Rayne Barton|title=The Green Hills Golf Chronicles|page=155|isbn=0738847917\n|passage=Even the lowly '''banana''' ball, the bane of so many weekenders, sometimes can be exactly right, as in this case.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2002|author=Andrew Collins|title=Guild of Honor|page=53|isbn=1403371490\n|passage=He played the fading, low-'''banana''' shot as planned, and the ball whistled left of the oak tree and between the pines.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=Richard Witzig|title=The Global Art of Soccer|page=247|isbn=0977668800\n|passage=[...]Bernd Schneider closed the scoring in injury-time with a 23 meter free-kick '''banana''' shot into the upper-right corner.}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{l|en|bunch}}\n* {{l|en|hand}}\n* [[Appendix:English collective nouns]]\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|en|bananas|pos=adj}}\n{{col|en\n|abaca\n|coconut<!--pejorative term-->\n|dining leaf\n|matoke\n|oreo<!--pejorative term-->\n|plantain\n|sinamay\n|waragi\n|Appendix:Colors\n}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aaabnn|Annaba}}\n\n{{C|en|Radioactivity|Potassium}}\n{{cln|en|3-syllable words}}\n{{c|en|Culture|Fruits|Genitalia|Racism|Yellows|Zingiberales order plants}}\n\n==Asturian==\n{{dercat|ast|wo|ar}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{ast-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ast-noun|f|bananes}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gl|fruit}}\n#: {{syn|ast|plátanu}}\n\n{{C|ast|Fruits}}\n\n==Catalan==\n{{dercat|ca|wo|ar}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n* {{audio|ca|LL-Q7026 (cat)-Unjoanqualsevol-banana.wav|a=Catalonia}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ca-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gloss|fruit}}\n#: {{syn|ca|plàtan}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|ca|bananer}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ca:IEC2}}\n\n{{C|ca|Fruits}}\n\n==Cornish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|kw|en|banana}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|kw|[baˈnaːna]|a=RMC}}\n* {{IPA|kw|[bəˈnæːnɐ]|a=RLC}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{kw-noun|m|s}}\n\n# [[#English|banana]]\n\n===Mutation===\n{{kw-mut}}\n\n{{C|kw|Fruits}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lyokoï-banana.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|fr|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fr|bananer||3|s|phis}} (to [[make a mistake]])\n\n==Galician==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{gl-pr}}\n* {{hyph|gl|ba|na|na}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{gl-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gl|fruit}}\n#: {{syn|gl|plátano}}\n#: {{ux|gl|Os chimpancés utilizan bastóns para coller unha '''banana'''.|Chimpanzees use sticks to pick up a '''banana'''.}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|gl|bananeira}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:gl:DRAG}}\n\n{{C|gl|Fruits}}\n\n==Icelandic==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{rhymes|is|aːnana|s=3}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|is|noun form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|is|bani||def|acc|p}}\n# {{inflection of|is|banani||indef|acc|;|indef|dat|s|;|indef|gen}}\n\n==Irish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|ga|wo|banaana}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ga|/bˠəˈn̪ˠan̪ˠə/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ga-noun|m|~|~í}}\n\n# [[#English|banana]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{ga-decl-m4|b|anana|ananaí}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|ga|crann bananaí|t=banana-tree}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{ga-mut}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ga:Ó Dónaill}}\n\n{{topics|ga|Fruits}}\n\n==Italian==\n{{wp|it:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|banàna<audio:LL-Q652 (ita)-Yiyi-banana.wav>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gloss|fruit}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|mt|banana|bor=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gloss|color}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{it-adj|inv=1}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gloss|color}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|it|banano}}\n\n{{C|it|Colors|Fruits}}\n\n==Japanese==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{ja-romaji}}\n\n# {{ja-romanization of|バナナ}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{internationalism|la}}. Vowel length cannot be properly ascribed, but the word-stress is surely on the second syllable.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA|banāna}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{la-noun|banāna<1>}}\n\n# {{lb|la|New Latin}} [[#English|banana]]\n#: {{syn|la|ariēna<q:Classical Latin, rare>|mūsa<q:Medieval Latin>}}\n#* {{quote-book|la|title=Americæ pars undecima: Seu descriptio admirandi itineris a Guilielmo Schouten Hollando peracti:{{nb...|Qua ratione in meridionali plaga freti Magellanici novum hactenusq́ue incognitum in mare Australe transitum patefecerit: Quas item terras, insulas, gentes, resq́ue mirabiles in dicto Australi Oceano obvias habuerit. Omnia elegantibus mappis, atque iconibus in æs incisis jam primùm illustrata, operâ & sumptibus Johann-Theodori de Bry Argentinensis.}}|location=Oppenheim|publisher=Typis Hieronymi Galleri|year=1619|page=41|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=RURbAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA41|passage=Illi amicabiliter ad navem noſtram appellentes, tantum Cocorum ac '''Bananarum''' nobis obtulerunt numerum, ut quilibet in navi nuces 50. duos '''Bananarum''' corbes eo die lucraretur.}}\n#* {{quote-book|la|author=[[w:Antonio de Herrera y Tordesillas|Antonio de Herrera {{quote-gloss|y Tordesillas}}]]|tlr=[[w:Caspar Barlaeus|C{{quote-gloss|aspar}} Barlæus]]|title=Novus Orbis, Sive Descriptio Indiae Occidentalis,{{nb...|Auctore Antonio de Herrera, Supremo Castellæ & Indiarum authoritate Philippi III. Hispaniarum Regis Historiographo. Metaphraste C. Barlæo. Accesserunt & aliorum Indiæ Occidentalis Descriptiones, & Navigationis nuperæ Australis Iacobi le Maire Historia, uti & navigationum omnium per Fretum Magellanicum succincta narratio.}}|location=Amsterdam|publisher=Apud Michaelem Colinium Bibliopolam, ad insigne Libri Domestici|year=1622|page=71|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=5yRjAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA71|passage=Tabaci, Cocorum, '''Bananarum''', oryzæ, piſorum, fabarum, porcorum, gallinarum & piſcium nobis faciebant copiam.}}\n#* {{quote-book|la|title=Voyage de la corvette l’Astrolabe&nbsp;: Exécuté pár ordre du roi, pendant les années 1826-1827-1828-1829, sous le commandement de M. J. Dumont d’Urville,{{nb...|capitaine de vaisseau. Publié par ordonnance de Sa Majesté. Histoire du voyage.}}|volume=IV|location=Paris|publisher=J. Tastu,{{nb...|éditeur, n. 4 bis, rue des Beaux-Arts.}}|year=1832|page=686|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/voyagedelacorvet0402dumo/page/686/mode/1up|passage=Hi Æthiopes monstrabant ut tormenta nostra exploderemus in canoas istas, sed significabatur ipsis, hoc à natura batava alienum, nocere inculpatis, si vero nos læderent, arma nobis data defensioni, nihilominus advolant amicè, adferentes tantam abundantiam ''cocorum'' et '''''bananarum''''', quantam desiderabamus, ut socio unicuique quinquaginta nuces distribuerentur et duo fasciculi '''bananarum'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|la|author=w:Francis William Newman<!--Preface: “taking only the general idea from Defoe”-->|title=Rebilius Cruso: {{w|Robinson Crusoe}}, in Latin; a Book to Lighten Tedium to a Learner|location=London|publisher=[[w:Nicholas Trübner|Trübner & Co.]],{{nb...|57 & 59, Ludgate Hill.}}|year=1884|page=56|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/rebiliuscrusorob00defo/page/56/mode/1up|passage=Jam dactylos, '''bananas''', cocos nuces, ananassas, uvas, ad libitum me habiturum spero: nimia me spes et nimia cupiditas festinavit. {{...}} Modicum '''bananarum''' et dactylorum onus assumo: vescor quantum libet, bibo e rivulo, et, relictâ scaphâ, ascendo vallem.}}\n#* {{quote-web|la|author=Erik Collins|chapter=Sample Lesson: Lesson plans for Capitulum VIII of Oerberg’s Lingua Latīna|work=[http://www.wheelockslatin.com/tutorials/TeachingMethods/teaching%20portfolios/Erik%20Collins%20Portfolio,%20artifacts%201.pdf LATIN 4770: Methods and Materials for Teaching Latin]|series=The Official [[w:Wheelock's Latin|Wheelock’s Latin]] Series Website|date=21 January 2010|passage=Post mēnsam, delīnā tabernārium in tabernā, quī māla et '''bananās''' vendit.|t=Behind the desk, draw in his shop a seller of apples and '''bananas'''.}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{la-ndecl|banāna<1>}}\n\n==Lower Sorbian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|dsb|de|Banane}}, ultimately from {{der|dsb|wo|banaana}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|dsb|/baˈnana/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{dsb-noun|f}}\n\n# [[#English|banana]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{dsb-decl-noun-1|banan}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:dsb:Starosta}}\n* {{R:WOLD|dsb|10}}\n\n{{C|dsb|Fruits}}\n\n==Maltese==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|mt|banan}}\n* {{alt|mt|fikabanana|figabanana||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|mt|:bor|it:banana|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|mt|/baˈnaː.na/|/baˈna.na/}}\n* {{rhymes|mt|ana|aːna|s=3}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{mt-coll-noun|sing=banana|pauc=bananiet}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gl|fruit}}\n\n{{C|mt|Foods|Fruits}}\n\n==Manchu==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{head|mnc|romanization|sc=Latn}}\n\n# {{romanization of|mnc|ᠪᠠᠨᠠᠨᠠ|t=banana}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|pt|id=fruit|:der|nic:-}}\n{{unk|pt|Borrowed}} from a {{bor|pt|nic|-}} language spoken in the [[Guinea]] region.<ref>{{R:pt:DELP-Nascentes|3|61|1}}</ref><ref>{{cite-web|url=https://dicionario.acad-ciencias.pt/pesquisa/?word=banana|work=Dicionário da Língua Portuguesa|entry=banana|author=Academia das Ciências de Lisboa|year=2001–present}}</ref> Further derivation is {{unc|pt|unclear}}. Possible ancestor or cognate languages include {{der|pt|wo|banaana}}, {{der|pt|emk|banana}}, and {{der|pt|vai|ꕒꘌꕯ}} or {{m|vai|ꕒꕌꕯ|tr=ɓaana}}.<ref>{{R:Dictionary.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite-book|page=144|url=https://archive.org/details/outlinesofgramma00koeluoft|title=Outlines of a Grammar of the Vei Language: Together with a Vei-English Vocabulary|author=S.W. Koelle|publisher=London Church Missionary House|year=1854}}</ref> However, ''Ay Baati Wolof'' (Munro & Gaye, 1997) posits that {{cog|wo|banaana}} is itself derived from Portuguese.<ref>{{cite-book|en|title=Ay baati Wolof: A Wolof dictionary|author=Munro, Pamela|author2=Gaye, Dieynaba|year=1997|oclc=938011184|url=https://linguistics.ucla.edu/publications/opl_19.pdf|location=Los Angeles|series=\nUCLA Occasional Papers in Linguistics|publisher=Department of Linguistics, University of California, Los Angeles|page=15}}</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|pt=+|br=+,bậnâhna}}\n* {{IPA|pt|/bɐ̃ˈnɐ̃.nɐ/|a=Northeast Brazil}}\n* {{rhyme|pt|ɐ̃nɐ|ɐnɐ|s=3}}\n* {{hyph|pt|ba|na|na}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gloss|fruit}}\n#: {{syn|pt|pacova<q:Brazil>}}\n#: {{ux|pt|As '''bananas''' são ricas em potássio|'''Bananas''' are high in potassium|inline=1}}\n# {{l|en|banana}} {{gloss|plant}}\n#: {{syn|pt|bananeira|q1=more common}}\n# {{lb|pt|informal}} [[penis]]\n# {{lb|pt|Brazil|informal}} [[bras d'honneur]] {{gloss|obscene gesture}}\n#: {{syn|pt|manguito|q1=Portugal}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pt\n|banana-comprida\n|banana-da-terra\n|banana-pão\n|república das bananas\n|república de bananas\n|banana de dinamite\n|bananeira\n|bananal\n|bananão\n|bananinha\n|embananar}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{top2}}\n* {{desc|nl|bor=1|banaan}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|en|bor=1|unc=1|banana}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|fr|bor=1|banane}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desctree|de|bor=1|Banane}}\n* {{desc|el|μπανάνα|der=1|unc=1}}\n* {{desc|lv|banāns|der=1|unc=1}}\n* {{desc|nb|der=1|unc=1|banan}}\n* {{desc|nn|der=1|unc=1|banan}}\n* {{desc|es|bor=1|unc=1|banana}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desctree|sv|der=1|unc=1|banan}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|mfbysense}}\n\n# {{lb|pt|pejorative|slang}} [[wimp]] {{gloss|a weak or unconfident person}}\n#: {{uxi|pt|Aquele rapaz é um '''banana'''!|That guy is a '''wimp'''!}}\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n{{C|pt|Fruits|Zingiberales order plants|Body language}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|ro|noun form|g=f}}\n\n# {{noun form of|ro|banană||def|s|nom//acc}} (banana (fruit))\n\n==Sardinian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|sc|es|banana}}, from {{der|sc|wo|banaana}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sc|/banana/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sc-noun|f|bananas}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}} (fruit)\n\n{{C|sc|Fruits}}\n{{c|sc|Foods}}\n\n==Serbo-Croatian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|sh|es|-}}, from {{der|sh|pt|-}}, from {{der|sh|wo|banaana}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sh|/banǎːna/}}\n* {{hyphenation|sh|ba|na|na}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sh-noun|banána|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|banana}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sh-decl-noun\n|banana|banane\n|banane|banana\n|banani|bananama\n|bananu|banane\n|banano|banane\n|banani|bananama\n|bananom|bananama\n}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:sh:HJP|eFtjXQ%3D%3D}}\n\n{{C|sh|Fruits|Zingiberales order plants}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|es|:der|nic:-|:bor<unc>|pt:banana}}\nDerived from a {{der|es|nic|-}} language spoken in the [[Guinea]] region,<ref>{{R:es:DCECH|volume=I|entry=banana|page=484}}</ref> probably through {{bor|es|pt|banana}}.<ref>{{cite-web|url=https://etimologias.dechile.net/?banana|year=2024|work=DECEL - Diccionario Etimológico Castellano en Línea|title=Etimología de BANANA}}</ref> Further derivation is {{unc|es|unclear}}. Possible ancestor or cognate languages include {{der|es|wo|banaana}}, {{der|es|emk|banana}}, and {{der|es|vai|ꕒꘌꕯ}} or {{m|vai|ꕒꕌꕯ|tr=ɓaana}}.<ref>{{R:Dictionary.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite-book|page=144|url=https://archive.org/details/outlinesofgramma00koeluoft|title=Outlines of a Grammar of the Vei Language: Together with a Vei-English Vocabulary|author=S.W. Koelle|publisher=London Church Missionary House|year=1854}}</ref> However, ''Ay Baati Wolof'' (Munro & Gaye, 1997) posits that {{cog|wo|banaana}} is itself derived from {{cog|pt|banana}}.<ref>{{cite-book|en|title=Ay baati Wolof: A Wolof dictionary|author=Munro, Pamela|author2=Gaye, Dieynaba|year=1997|oclc=938011184|url=https://linguistics.ucla.edu/publications/opl_19.pdf|location=Los Angeles|series=\nUCLA Occasional Papers in Linguistics|publisher=Department of Linguistics, University of California, Los Angeles|page=15}}</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|+<audio:LL-Q1321 (spa)-Rubýñ-banana.wav<a:Costa Rica>>}}\n\n===Noun===\n[[File:Porpaís banana plátano.svg|thumb|Terms for banana in Latin America]]\n{{es-noun|f}}\n\n# {{lb|es|Rioplatense|Andes|Guatemala|Honduras}} {{l|en|banana}} {{gloss|fruit}}\n#: {{syn|es|plátano|guineo|cambur|banano}}\n# {{lb|es|Uruguay|colloquial}} an [[idiot]]\n#: {{syn|es|idiota}}\n# {{lb|es|Argentina|Dominican Republic|colloquial}} [[smartass]]\n#: {{syn|es|sabihondo}}\n# {{lb|es|Bolivia|Guatemala|Costa Rica|Honduras|colloquial}} [[penis]]\n#: {{syn|es|Thesaurus:pene}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* ''banana'' may also be used in Spain, to differentiate from {{m|es|plátano|t=plantain}}; otherwise, ''plátano'' refers to either.\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|es|banano|bananero}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|bor=1|unc=1|banana}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|lv|der=1|unc=1|banāns}}\n* {{desc|nb|der=1|unc=1|banan}}\n* {{desc|nn|der=1|unc=1|banan}}\n* {{desc|sh|der=1}}\n** {{desc|sh|бана́на|sclang=1}}\n** {{desc|sh|banána|sclang=1}}\n* {{desctree|sv|der=1|unc=1|banan}}\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n{{C|es|Fruits}}\n\n==Tok Pisin==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|tpi|wo|es|pt}}\nFrom {{der|tpi|en|banana}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|tpi|noun}}\n\n# [[#English|banana]]\n#* {{quote-book|tpi|worklang=en|year=1995\n|author=John Verhaar\n|title=Toward a reference grammar of Tok Pisin: an experiment in corpus linguistics\n|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=4DeKkIzS8B4C&pg=PA433#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|isbn=0-8248-1672-2\n|page=433\n|passage=Mekim olsem pinis, orait tupela i planim taro na '''banana''', na kumu, painap, kon, tomato, na kaukau tu.}}\n\n{{C|tpi|Fruits}}\n\n==Welsh==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|cy|en|banana}}, from {{der|cy|wo|banaana}}, via Portuguese and/or Spanish.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|cy|/baˈnana/|a=cy-N}}\n* {{IPA|cy|/baˈna(ː)na/|a=cy-S}}\n* {{rhymes|cy|ana|s=3}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cy-noun|f|bananas}}\n\n# [[#English|banana]]\n#: {{syn|cy|[[ffrwchnedd]]en|q=humorous}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|cy|twinc bananas||bananquit}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{cy-mut}}\n\n{{C|cy|Fruits}}"}}